        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Exodus 25</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l><emph>Parashat Terumah</emph></l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                        <l n="1">And the Lord spoke
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            to Moses, saying,</l>
                        <l n="2">‘Speak
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            to the children of Israel, that they by themselves shall take and offer
                            <milestone unit="page" n="126v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            me heave offerings. From every man whose heart would make him generous
                            you shall take a
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            heave offering.</l>
                        <l n="3">And this is the contribution which you shall take
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            of them: gold, and silver, and bronze,</l>
                        <l n="4">And blue and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            purple and scarlet silk, and linen, and goats’ hair,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="5">And rams’ skins dyed red, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            porpoise skins, and acacia wood,</l>
                        <l n="6">Oil
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            for the light, spices for anointing oil and for the fragrant
                            incense,</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                        <l n="7">Onyx stones for the ephod, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            stones to be set for the breastplate.</l>
                        <l n="8">And let them make me a sanctuary,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            and my divine Presence will dwell among them.</l>
                        <l n="9">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            According to all that I show you: the appearance of the tabernacle
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            and the appearance of all the vessels of it — so shall you do.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                        <l n="10">And they shall make an ark of acacia wood:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            two cubits and a half the length of it, and a cubit and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            a half the breadth of it, and a cubit and a half the height of it.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                        <l n="11">And you shall overlay it with pure gold, inside and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            outside shall you overlay it, and shall make on it a moulding of gold
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            all around it.</l>
                        <l n="12">And you shall cast four rings
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            of gold for it, and put them in the four corners of it,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            and two rings shall be on the one side of it, and two rings
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            on the second side of it.</l>
                        <l n="13">And you shall make
                            <milestone unit="page" n="127r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            poles of acacia wood, and overlay them with gold.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                        <l n="14">And you shall put the poles into the rings
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            by the sides of the ark, to carry the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            ark by them.</l>
                        <l n="15">The
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            poles shall be in the rings of the ark: they shall not depart from
                            it.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                        <l n="16">And you shall place in the ark the law that I shall give
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            you.</l>
                        <l n="17">And you shall make a cover of pure gold:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            two cubits <supplied reason="lost">and a half</supplied><ref
                                target="#fn1" type="noteAnchor" /> the length of it, and a cubit and
                            a half the breadth
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            of it.</l>
                        <l n="18">And you shall make two cherubim of gold,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            shall you make them of hammered work, at the two ends of the <delSpan
                                spanTo="#del001" />breastplate<anchor xml:id="del001" />
                            <addSpan spanTo="#add001" /><emph>cover</emph><anchor xml:id="add001"
                             />.</l>
                        <l n="19">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            make one cherub on the end, on this side, and one cherub on the end, on this
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            side of the cover. You shall make the cherubim on the two ends
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            of it.</l>
                        <l n="20">And the cherubim shall
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            spread out their wings above, encircling the cover with their wings,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            and their faces shall face one another:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            the faces of the cherubim shall be toward the cover.</l>
                        <l n="21">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            And you shall put the cover on top of the ark, from above,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            and you shall place in the ark the testimony that I shall give you.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                        <l n="22">And my divine Presence will always be ready to appear
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            to you there, and I will speak with you from above the cover,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            from between the two cherubim that are on the ark of the
                            <milestone unit="page" n="127v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            law, everything that I shall convey through you to the children
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            of Israel.</l>
                        <l n="23">And you shall make a table of acacia wood:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            two cubits the length of it, and a cubit the breadth of it, and a cubit and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            a half the height of it.</l>
                        <l n="24">And you shall overlay it with pure gold
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            and make for it a moulding of gold all around it.</l>
                        <l n="25">And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            you shall make for it a border |of| a hand|breadth| around it, and you
                            shall make a moulding of gold
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            for the border all around.</l>
                        <l n="26">And you shall make for it
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            four rings of gold, and put the rings on
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            the four corners that are at its four legs.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="27">The rings shall be opposite to the border
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            as places for the poles to carry the table.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                        <l n="28">And you shall make the poles of acacia wood
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            and overlay them with gold, and the table shall be carried
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            with these.</l>
                        <l n="29">And you shall make its bowls,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            and its spoons, and its <supplied reason="lost"
                                >†tablecloths</supplied><ref target="#fn2" type="noteAnchor" />, and its
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            <seg type="commented" corresp="#seg001" />cloths with which it shall be
                                covered<anchor type="commented" xml:id="seg001" /><ref target="#fn3"
                                type="noteAnchor" />, of pure gold shall you make them.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                        <l n="30">And you shall place showbread on the table
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            before me always.</l>
                        <l n="31">And you shall make a lampstand of pure
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            gold. The lampstand shall be made of hammered work — its shaft and its branches,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            its cups, its knobs, and its leaves shall be of the one same |piece|
                            –</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                        <l n="32">And six branches come out of the sides of it: three
                            <milestone unit="page" n="128r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            branches of the lampstand out of one side, and three branches of the lampstand
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            out of the second side.</l>
                        <l n="33">Three cups coupled,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            a knob and a leaf in one branch, and three cups coupled,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            with a knob and a leaf in one branch. So it is for the six
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            branches that come out of the lampstand.</l>
                        <l n="34">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            And in the lampstand shall be <delSpan spanTo="#del002" />three<anchor
                                xml:id="del002" />
                            <addSpan spanTo="#add002" /><emph>four</emph><anchor xml:id="add002" />
                            cups coupled, with their knobs and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            their leaves.</l>
                        <l n="35">And a knob under the two branches
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            of the same one piece, and a knob under the two branches
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            of the same one piece, and a knob under the two branches
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            of the same one piece — for the six branches that come out
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            of the lampstand.</l>
                        <l n="36">Their knobs and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            their branches shall be of the same piece, all of it shall be one
                            hammered work
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            of pure gold.</l>
                        <l n="37">And you shall make its seven places for candles:
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            <seg type="commented" corresp="#seg002" />and the priest shall light its candles,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            that they may give light next to his face<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="seg002" /><ref target="#fn4" type="noteAnchor" />.</l>
                        <l n="38">And its tongs,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            and their censers of pure gold.</l>
                        <l n="39">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            He shall make it — all these vessels — of a kantar of pure gold.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                        <l n="40">And see and make them after their patterns
                            <milestone unit="line" xml:id="line-19-1" n="19" next="ADub.III.73.002.026.trl.xml#line-19-2" />
                            that you are shown in the mountain.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app>
                        <note xml:id="fn1" type="footnote">K: deest; a scribal error, cf. Heb.
                                <foreign xml:lang="he" style="unicode-bidi: embed;">אַמָּתַיִם
                                וָחֵצִי </foreign>
                            ‘two cubits and a half’.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn2" type="footnote">An uncertain translation of
                                <emph>stolpec</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn3" type="footnote">K: <emph>arytqyč</emph>; there is an
                            elaborate explanation of this item in Exo 37:16.</note>
                        <note xml:id="fn4" type="footnote">Interpretative translation.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
